Package: finalPackage
Type: Package
Title: Statistical Functions for Biomedical Informatics
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Yuqing Duan
Maintainer: Yuqing Duan <yuqing.duan@emory.edu>
Description: The package contains several statistical functions useful for biomedical research, 
    including calculating maximum likelihood estimates of Bernoulli distributions, survival curve estimation, scaling and unscaling data, 
    principal component analysis approximation, standardization of variable names in a dataset, calculating minimum sample sizes for t-tests, 
    and downloading reports from RedCap. Each function is accompanied by examples and detailed instructions for use.
